                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32786,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 46923,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_rehnquist.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12293,
                            "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.519,
                                "byte_start": 84251,
                                "byte_stop": 118419,
                                "text": "I have the opinion of the Court to announce in No. 99-5525, Dickerson against United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 8.519,
                                "stop": 14.911,
                                "byte_start": 118419,
                                "byte_stop": 143915,
                                "text": "You have the right to remain silent; anything you say can be used against you in the court of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.911,
                                "stop": 17.649,
                                "byte_start": 143915,
                                "byte_stop": 154886,
                                "text": "You have the right to the presence of an attorney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.649,
                                "stop": 22.301,
                                "byte_start": 154886,
                                "byte_stop": 173485,
                                "text": "If you cannot afford an attorney, one will be provided for you prior to any questioning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.301,
                                "stop": 24.332,
                                "byte_start": 173485,
                                "byte_stop": 181635,
                                "text": "If you so desire."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.332,
                                "stop": 29.183,
                                "byte_start": 181635,
                                "byte_stop": 201071,
                                "text": "These four warnings that accord to police stations and on television screens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.183,
                                "stop": 34.496,
                                "byte_start": 201071,
                                "byte_stop": 222282,
                                "text": "In the 34 years since we decided the case of Miranda versus Arizona."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.496,
                                "stop": 46.562,
                                "byte_start": 222282,
                                "byte_stop": 270556,
                                "text": "In that opinion we held that any statement a suspect makes while in police custody is not admissible in the prosecution\u2019s case in chief, unless the statement was preceded by these warnings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.562,
                                "stop": 55.692,
                                "byte_start": 270556,
                                "byte_stop": 307023,
                                "text": "The present case Dickerson addresses whether Miranda has been superseded by an Act of Congress passed in 1968."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.692,
                                "stop": 64.708,
                                "byte_start": 307023,
                                "byte_stop": 343177,
                                "text": "We hold that Miranda is a constitutional decision that may not be overruled by Congress and we decline to overrule Miranda ourselves."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.708,
                                "stop": 73.816,
                                "byte_start": 343177,
                                "byte_stop": 379539,
                                "text": "We therefore hold that Miranda and its progeny continue to govern the admissibility of statements made during custodial interrogation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.816,
                                "stop": 79.537,
                                "byte_start": 379539,
                                "byte_stop": 402422,
                                "text": "Petitioner Charles Dickerson was indicted for bank robbery and related federal crimes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.537,
                                "stop": 89.375,
                                "byte_start": 402422,
                                "byte_stop": 441815,
                                "text": "Before trial he moved to suppress an incriminatory statement he made at an FBI Field Office on the ground that he had not received Miranda warnings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.375,
                                "stop": 92.626,
                                "byte_start": 441815,
                                "byte_stop": 454772,
                                "text": "The District Court granted his motion to suppress."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.626,
                                "stop": 112.672,
                                "byte_start": 454772,
                                "byte_stop": 535020,
                                "text": "On appeal, the Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit agreed that his statement was taken in violation of Miranda, but concluded that the statement should nevertheless be admitted because Miranda had been superseded by 18 U.S.C. Section 3501, a statute passed by Congress in 1968."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.672,
                                "stop": 124.991,
                                "byte_start": 535020,
                                "byte_stop": 584235,
                                "text": "Section 3501 displays Miranda\u2019s specific warnings requirement with a test that looks to whether given the totality of the circumstances surrounding a suspect\u0027s statement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.991,
                                "stop": 128.383,
                                "byte_start": 584235,
                                "byte_stop": 597818,
                                "text": "The statement was voluntarily given."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.383,
                                "stop": 135.056,
                                "byte_start": 597818,
                                "byte_stop": 624568,
                                "text": "Because of the importance of the issues raised by the Court of Appeals decision we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.056,
                                "stop": 143.255,
                                "byte_start": 624568,
                                "byte_stop": 657273,
                                "text": "It\u2019s well-established that the Constitution proscribes the admission of any confession that is obtained involuntarily."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.255,
                                "stop": 159.7,
                                "byte_start": 657273,
                                "byte_stop": 723102,
                                "text": "We have never abandoned that requirement, but since Miranda, in 1966, we have also enforced the rule that any custodial statement must be preceded by specific warnings to be admissible in the prosecutions case in chief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.7,
                                "stop": 174.615,
                                "byte_start": 723102,
                                "byte_stop": 782765,
                                "text": "Because 3501, the Act of Congress seeks to abandon Miranda\u2019s warning requirement and return to voluntariness, this case turns on whether Congress has constitutional authority to supersede Miranda."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.615,
                                "stop": 177.128,
                                "byte_start": 782765,
                                "byte_stop": 792796,
                                "text": "The law in this area is clear."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.128,
                                "stop": 191.743,
                                "byte_start": 792796,
                                "byte_stop": 851311,
                                "text": "Congress has authority to supersede non constitutional judicially created rules of evidence and procedure, but Congress may not legislatively overrule our decisions interpreting and applying the Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.743,
                                "stop": 206.342,
                                "byte_start": 851311,
                                "byte_stop": 909720,
                                "text": "The dispositive question therefore is whether the Miranda court announced a constitutional rule or merely exercised its supervisory authority to regulate evidence in the absence of Congressional direction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.342,
                                "stop": 211.843,
                                "byte_start": 909720,
                                "byte_stop": 931663,
                                "text": "For a number of reasons we think it clear that Miranda\u2019s rule is constitutionally based."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.843,
                                "stop": 219.69,
                                "byte_start": 931663,
                                "byte_stop": 963115,
                                "text": "First, both Miranda and two of its companion cases applied the new warning requirements to proceedings in State Courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.69,
                                "stop": 230.044,
                                "byte_start": 963115,
                                "byte_stop": 1004493,
                                "text": "We do not have a supervisory power over the courts of the State and may only require those tribunals to comply with the dictates of the Federal Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.044,
                                "stop": 239.044,
                                "byte_start": 1004493,
                                "byte_stop": 1040437,
                                "text": "Second, the Miranda opinion itself is replete with statements indicating that the Court thought it was announcing a constitutional rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.044,
                                "stop": 254.638,
                                "byte_start": 1040437,
                                "byte_stop": 1102818,
                                "text": "Third, while the Miranda Court invited legislative action to protect the constitutional right against self-incrimination, it specified that such legislation must be effective in apprising the accused of their right of silence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.638,
                                "stop": 264.156,
                                "byte_start": 1102818,
                                "byte_stop": 1140956,
                                "text": "The fact that our post Miranda cases have made exceptions from its rule does not demonstrate that Miranda was not a constitutional decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.156,
                                "stop": 274.377,
                                "byte_start": 1140956,
                                "byte_stop": 1181812,
                                "text": "These decisions illustrate the principle not that Miranda is not a constitutional rule, but that no constitutional rule is immutable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 274.377,
                                "stop": 283.012,
                                "byte_start": 1181812,
                                "byte_stop": 1216398,
                                "text": "No court laying down a general rule can possibly foresee the various circumstances in which counsel will seek to apply it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.012,
                                "stop": 292.222,
                                "byte_start": 1216398,
                                "byte_stop": 1253178,
                                "text": "The sort of modifications represented by these cases are as much a normal part of constitutional law as the original decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 292.222,
                                "stop": 298.82,
                                "byte_start": 1253178,
                                "byte_stop": 1279614,
                                "text": "We reject the arguments of Section 3501 complies with Miranda\u2019s requirement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 298.82,
                                "stop": 305.27,
                                "byte_start": 1279614,
                                "byte_stop": 1305423,
                                "text": "The legislative alternative be equally as effective in preventing coerced confessions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 305.27,
                                "stop": 324.415,
                                "byte_start": 1305423,
                                "byte_stop": 1382014,
                                "text": "There are more measures enforced today than there were in 1966 to allow some of these protections, but Section 3501 expressly abandons the requirement of pre-interrogation warnings in favor of the totality of the circumstances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 324.415,
                                "stop": 335.597,
                                "byte_start": 1382014,
                                "byte_stop": 1426736,
                                "text": "It simply does not comply with Miranda\u2019s intimation that other methods, other than those four warnings, would satisfy the constitutional demand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 335.597,
                                "stop": 342.498,
                                "byte_start": 1426736,
                                "byte_stop": 1454321,
                                "text": "Having concluded that Congress may not overrule Miranda, we decline to overrule it ourselves."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 342.498,
                                "stop": 355.563,
                                "byte_start": 1454321,
                                "byte_stop": 1506566,
                                "text": "Whether or not, we would agree with Miranda\u2019s reasoning and its resulting rule, were we addressing the issue in the first instance, the principles of stare decisis weigh heavily against overruling it now."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 355.563,
                                "stop": 364.291,
                                "byte_start": 1506566,
                                "byte_stop": 1541466,
                                "text": "Miranda has become embedded in routine police practices to the point where the warnings that become part of our national culture."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 364.291,
                                "stop": 370.563,
                                "byte_start": 1541466,
                                "byte_stop": 1566543,
                                "text": "While we have overruled our precedents when subsequent cases have undermined their doctrinal underpinnings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 370.563,
                                "stop": 374.598,
                                "byte_start": 1566543,
                                "byte_stop": 1582739,
                                "text": "We do not believe that this has happened to the Miranda decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 374.598,
                                "stop": 385.949,
                                "byte_start": 1582739,
                                "byte_stop": 1628088,
                                "text": "If anything, our subsequent cases have reduced the impact of the Miranda rule on legitimate law enforcement while reaffirming the decision\u2019s core ruling."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 385.949,
                                "stop": 401.891,
                                "byte_start": 1628088,
                                "byte_stop": 1691827,
                                "text": "The disadvantage of the Miranda rule is that statements which may be by no means involuntary made by a defendant who is aware of his rights, may nonetheless be excluded and a guilty defendant go free as a result."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 401.891,
                                "stop": 419.714,
                                "byte_start": 1691827,
                                "byte_stop": 1763193,
                                "text": "But experience suggests that the totality-of-the-circumstances test which Section 3501 seeks to revive is more difficult than Miranda for law enforcement officers to conform to, and for courts to apply in a consistent manner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 419.714,
                                "stop": 443.936,
                                "byte_start": 1763193,
                                "byte_stop": 1860055,
                                "text": "The requirement that Miranda warnings be given does not, of course dispense with the voluntariness inquiry, but as we have said in a previous case, cases in which a defendant can make a colorable argument that a self-incriminating statement was compelled despite the fact that the law enforcement authorities adhered to the dictates of Miranda are rare."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 443.936,
                                "stop": 447.961,
                                "byte_start": 1860055,
                                "byte_stop": 1876147,
                                "text": "For all these reasons the judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 447.961,
                                "stop": 452.833,
                                "byte_start": 1876147,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Thomas has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
